oking\nfor business investments begin\nto arrive, as they surely will\nwithin the next thirty days,\nwhat are we going to do with\nthem'.' How are we going to\n\"explanation ourselves\" and\nlake care of them in a manner\nthey desire andar\u00e9 willing to\npay for? With these same ar\nrivals will come a great number\nof those suffering in the last\nstages of tuberculosis. The\nFraternal City sanatorium will\nlake only those who have a\nchance for recovery, but unfor\ntunately human nature i much\nthe same the world over, and\nin a large percent of such cases\nthey delay too long in mailing a\nchange toa more equable climate.\nThe result will be that hundreds\nof such sufferers will be scatter\ned broadcast throughout Alamo\ngordo, in boarding houses ami\nl ooms, none of them under medi\ncal surveillance and the resultant\nconditions will shortly make our\nbeautiful city a place of conta\ngion and dread. This condition\ncan be met and overcome by or\nganizing a stock company to\nmild ami operate a sanatorium\nthat will lake I luxe Millering\nand hapaiaaaff ill pajMM and\nare f.,r them under proper medi-,\nal dirertion and at a price that\nwill enable almost any to enter\nthe institution. Aside from the\nprote ti. ,u it wnuld allord the on-1\ntire city, it would be a huaineaa\ninvestment that will net the\nowner- not le t han M per cent\nper year upon the investment, i\nTie tigures are not mere idle\nPM but are the result of a\ncareful and actual estimate\nmade by those who know their!\n(HisinaM. Home wise man will\nhear fortune knocking at bis\ndoor and will take up the neces\nsity for small cottages to rent,\nand he should go at the plan in\nan intelligent manner and se-j\ncur.' a tract of ground, say ml\nfeet front by ISO deep, and ar\nrange the cottages on three sides,\not a hollow square facing the\n-tree! and have a central garden\nSpot on w hieh all the houses will\nlace. With a piece of ground\nthis size he can build eleven,\nlive-room one-story cottages,\nnone of w hich would be closer\nthan twenty feet, and these cot\ntages would easily rent for $20 a\nmonth if they had modern con\nveniences, and every one would\nbe occupied constantly. The\nground would cost $1000 and the\n(deven houses and accessories\nwould cost $18,000 additional.\nThis would make the investment\n$19,000 on which the income\nwould be $2,640, or II per cent\nper annum. Is not this good\nenough for some one to take up?\nBUSINESS PROSPECTS ARE GOOD\nLeading Alamo Merchant Tells of Won\nderful Increase In Business.\nThat Alamogordo is growing and the\nsurrounding country being settled rap\nIdly, and by a substantial class ot set\ntlers Is best evidenced by the volume ot\nbusiness trani\u00e1cted by Alamogordo\nmerchant! and the Increase in deposits\nill the banks.\nMr. K. H, Cox, who conducts a large\ngrocery, dry goods, clothing and shoe\nbusiness on New York avenue, In dis\ncussing the business outlook for the\ncoming year, made the following state\nment: our expectations during the year\nhave more than beeu realized, it being\nnecessary tor us to replenish some of the\nlines we carry, such as dry goods, shoes\nand men's clothing several times, to sup\nply the demand. We notice that the peo\npie coining to Alamogordo are shrewd\nOlivers and demand lirst class goods.\nTu this fact can he attributed our unu\nsually larg business, as we sell all our\ngoods at a small margin of prolit. As\na result of this method our sales are\nenormous and no out-of-date goods ever\naccumulate In our store. At present we\nare selling a large portion of our stock\nj at cost in order to make room for our\n-tuck uf new fatl goods, which we ex\npect any day. Taken as a whole, I am\nwell pleased with the business of the\npa-', year and expect it to double the\ncoming year.''\nMr. Cos is one of the leading business\nmen of Alamogordo and his prophesy\nfor increased prosperity during the com\ning year can be depended upon.\nPARKER'S\nPOOL AND\nBILLIARD HALL\nFINE TABLES AND\nPROMPT SERVICE\nThis fat boy would thiol\nIt impossible to lint1\nclothes to lit him. If :oo\nmerchant could lit hln\nthe fat hoy wouldn I\nknow of It 'unless tin\nmerchant advert ised tin\nfact. We have lots of fftl\nhovs. and tliev can Bnd\nthe luerciiaiit's uiiuieun pago 4, this iMUe\nam Waatea- far Itatrl-\nSTOVE S\nI have the largest and most complete\nstock of stoves in the southwest at\nprices that are so low they won't last\nGEO. WARNOCK Alamogordo, N. M.\nGOVERNMENT WILL PROBABLY ASSIST\nThe Alamogordo Kusjness\nMen's etch is anxious to secure\nsix ripe sugar heets to lie atad\nfor testing parpo l, in connec\ntion with having the government\nmake un appropriation for a very\nextensive experimental planting\nat Alamogordo. Anyone having\nripe sugar heets will kindly\nbring six U) the News office fori\nthe above mentioned purposes.\nTIBBETT'B HOME SOLD.\nMr. Charles E. Mitchell, president of\nthe Citizen's National bank of Alamo\ngordo, lias purchased the property of\nthe late Arthur N. Tibbelts, on New I\nVork avenue and Thirteenth street.\nThis property Is an ideal home, Mr. i\nTibbetts having built it for his own\nresidence, but his sudden and untimely\ndeatli prevented his ever having occu\npied the house.\nWell Casing for Sale.\nI have just received a large car load\nof well casing, standard sizes, and can\nmake extremely close quotations for im\nmediate deliveries. M. H. I'Msiinr, Alamogordo.\nCarter Brothers\nContracts Taaea, Any Site or Location.\nALAWOGORDO. NEW MEXICO\nHOICK 0 DIETER CO.\nIMPORTERS AND WHOLESALE\nLIQUOR DEALERS\nWe Make a Specialty of STRAIGHT WHISKY,\nBoth Bulk and Bottled in Bond.\nEL PHSO\nTEXHS\nHOTEL ALAMOGORDO\n$3 Per Day. Special Rates by the Week or Month.\nAll Outside Rooms. Porter Meets All Trains.\nTHE ALAMOGORDO PRINTING is prepared,\nwith new equipment and highly skilled printers, to\ndo printing of any character, either commercial or for\nprivate use, and carries a stock that will lill any demand.\nWe produce work that will compare favorably with that\ndone in any part of the country.\nLegal work and blanks, stationery, circulars, catalogs,\nembossed and die work, wedding invitations, programs.\nDo You Want A Home?\nWe own and olfer for sale some of the best business and residence property in\nAlamogordo, ranging in prices from $1,(100 to 80,000, according to size and loca\ntion of house.\nDESIRABLE RESIDENCE LOTS\nIn all parts of the city will be sold at Rook Bottom Prices. Jnst make a small\npayment down and the rest can be paid monthly until your lot is paid fir. Every\ntime a dollar is invested In Heal Estate it Is a dollar saved, and there is no city In\nsouthern New Mexico, that can offer a brighter fnlnre and better investment\nthan Alamogordo Ueal Estate. The place Is noted for its fine park, beautiful\nhomes, splendid shade trees, and its unlimited supply of pure mountain spring\nwater.\nIF YOU ARE IN THE MARKET\nto buy a cottage, large residence, business house, vacant lot, acre property, val\nley or mountain farm, or to rent store, warehouse, residence, large or small, call\nand see us. No trouble to answer question or show property.\nDO YOU WANT TO RENT?\nWe have for rent at this time live desirable vacant houses ranging in size from\nthree to five rooms each: all of these houses are now being painted and decorated.\nKent from SO toSl-'per month.\nA borne in Alamogordo is a homo in the best place, with the best people, where\nwe have the best climate and purest water in the Southwest.\nCIGARS, TOBACCO and\nSMOKERS' SUPPLIES\nSouth Side I Oth St., Alamogordo\nAlamogordo Improvement Company\nW. R. Eidson, Vice President and General Manager","height":"22604","width":"13556"}}
